# Neovim Multi-Cursor Workflow

## Adding Cursors

Alt+k                    # Add cursor below (down)
Alt+i                    # Add cursor above (up)
Ctrl+d                   # Add cursor on next match of word under cursor
Ctrl+Shift+l             # Select all occurrences of word
Leader+c+c               # Add cursor at current position
Leader+c (visual)        # Add cursor on each selected line

## Movement in Multi-Cursor Mode

### Basic Movement (IJKL)
i                        # Move up
k                        # Move down
j                        # Move left
l                        # Move right

### Word Movement
L (Shift+L)              # Next word (like VSCode Alt+Right)
J (Shift+J)              # Previous word (like VSCode Alt+Left)

### Line Movement
$                        # End of line (like VSCode Cmd+Right)
0                        # Start of line - column 0
^                        # First non-blank character

### Fast Movement
K (Shift+K)              # Move 5 lines down
I (Shift+I)              # Move 5 lines up

## Editing at Multiple Cursors

e                        # Enter insert mode at all cursors
a                        # Append after cursor at all cursors
x                        # Delete character at all cursors
c                        # Change/replace (then move to select what to change)
d                        # Delete (then move to select what to delete)

## Selection & Advanced

v                        # Start visual selection mode (select as you move)
Ctrl+x                   # Skip current match (when adding with Ctrl+d)
Ctrl+p                   # Remove last cursor
u                        # Undo in multi-cursor mode
Esc                      # Exit multi-cursor mode

## Common Workflows

### Replace word in multiple places
1. Cursor on word
2. Ctrl+d (repeat to add more occurrences)
3. e (enter insert mode)
4. Type replacement
5. Esc

### Edit end of multiple lines
1. Visual select lines
2. Leader+c (add cursor per line)
3. $ (go to end of line)
4. a (append mode)
5. Type text
6. Esc

### Change multiple function names
1. Cursor on function name
2. Ctrl+Shift+l (select all)
3. e (insert mode)
4. Type new name
5. Esc

### Add text after specific words
1. Search for word: /pattern
2. n to find first occurrence
3. Ctrl+d to add more
4. L (move word forward if needed)
5. a (append)
6. Type text
7. Esc

## VSCode to Neovim Translation

| VSCode Action           | Neovim Equivalent  |
|------------------------|-------------------|
| Cmd+Alt+Down           | Alt+k             |
| Cmd+Alt+Up             | Alt+i             |
| Cmd+D                  | Ctrl+d            |
| Cmd+Shift+L            | Ctrl+Shift+l      |
| Alt+Left (word back)   | J (Shift+J)       |
| Alt+Right (word fwd)   | L (Shift+L)       |
| Cmd+Left (line start)  | 0 or ^            |
| Cmd+Right (line end)   | $                 |
| Type to replace        | e then type       |

## Key Difference: Position First, Then Edit

VSCode: Select while moving with Shift
Neovim: Position cursors, then enter insert/edit mode

Example:
- VSCode: Shift+Alt+Right+Right (select 2 words)
- Neovim: L L e (move 2 words, then insert)
